By Daniel Dada CHI Limited, a food and beverage manufacturer in Nigeria, has unveiled 85-gramme packs for its SuperBite sausage roll and Beefie Beef Roll. In a statement yesterday, the company said the new 85g pack sizes target consumers seeking to enjoy more of the sausage and snack. It said the new and bigger 85g pack sizes join the 45g pack sizes to offer consumers the power of choice for satisfaction and are available for quick meals, gifts for loved ones, in-between-work meals, in traffic, and for entertaining guests during visits. In her comment on the new packs, the Marketing Director at CHI Limited, Mrs Toyin Nnodi, said the new SuperBite Premium Sausage Roll and Beefie Beef Roll 85g pack sizes were introduced to give consumers the power of choice for satisfaction in a pack size. “We are delighted with the introduction of the SuperBite Premium Sausage Roll and Beefie Beef Roll 85g pack sizes and confident that it will offer a more satisfying snacking experience and choice to everyone who has enjoyed the current pack size,” she said. Mrs Nnodi noted that the products are at mobile vendor points in traffic, CHI Shoppe, neighborhood kiosks and at departmental stores nationwide.